{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17633873","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17633873"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T17:58:35+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T17:58:35+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17507"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"17507","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/17507"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.42,0.05,0.42,0.11,0]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10197"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78545"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10197","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10197"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17507"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"63886"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4928"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"10053"},{"type":"tags","id":"10066"},{"type":"tags","id":"10079"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"23866"},{"type":"contributions","id":"23874"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78545","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/78545"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the first enzymatic step in glycogen synthesis from glucose?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Conversion of glucose-6-phosphate to glucose-1-phosphate","Formation of UDP-glucose from glucose-1-phosphate","Phosphorylation of glucose by hexokinase","Formation of alpha-1,4-glycosidic bonds","Creation of branch points by branching enzyme"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe first enzymatic step in glycogen synthesis is the \u003Cstrong\u003Ephosphorylation of glucose by hexokinase\u003C/strong\u003E (or glucokinase in liver cells) to form glucose-6-phosphate. This ATP-dependent reaction is essential to trap glucose within the cell and begin the glycogen synthesis pathway.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EConversion of glucose-6-phosphate to glucose-1-phosphate\u003C/strong\u003E - This is the second step in the pathway, catalysed by phosphoglucomutase\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFormation of UDP-glucose from glucose-1-phosphate\u003C/strong\u003E - This occurs after glucose-1-phosphate formation\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFormation of alpha-1,4-glycosidic bonds\u003C/strong\u003E - This occurs later in the pathway and is catalysed by glycogen synthase\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECreation of branch points by branching enzyme\u003C/strong\u003E - This is one of the final steps in glycogen synthesis\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAfter the initial hexokinase reaction, glucose-6-phosphate is converted to glucose-1-phosphate, which is then activated to UDP-glucose before being incorporated into the growing glycogen chain.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Glycogen synthesis begins with phosphorylation of glucose to glucose-6-phosphate by hexokinase/glucokinase.","Subsequent steps include conversion to glucose-1-phosphate by phosphoglucomutase and formation of UDP-glucose.","The final structure requires both alpha-1,4 and alpha-1,6-glycosidic bonds to form branched glycogen."],"references":["Tortora GJ, Derrickson BH, Burkett B, Peoples G, Dye D, Cooke J, et al. Principles of Anatomy and Physiology, 2nd Asia-Pacific Edition: John Wiley \u0026 Sons, Limited; 2019","Adeva-Andany MM, Gonz\u00e1lez-Luc\u00e1n M, Donapetry-Garc\u00eda C, Fern\u00e1ndez-Fern\u00e1ndez C, Ameneiros-Rodr\u00edguez E. Glycogen metabolism in humans. BBA Clin. 2016;5:85-100. doi: 10.1016/j.bbacli.2016.02.001. PMID: 27051594; PMCID: PMC4802397."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"63886"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17507"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"63886","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/63886"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-11T12:56:46+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-11T12:57:50+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10197"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78545"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"7"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"4928","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/4928"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udca9"